INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'c75d2a43-9657-4320-806a-3649eb027803',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Spring Boot Testing — Unit vs Integration, HTTP Mocking, and Test Database Strategy$escape$,
  $escape$Spring Boot's testing pyramid has three distinct layers. Unit tests target service logic in isolation using `@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)` — no Spring context loaded, fast feedback. Integration tests use `@SpringBootTest` to wire the full context; combine with `@AutoConfigureTestDatabase(replace = NONE)` and Testcontainers to spin a real PostgreSQL instance instead of H2, avoiding SQL dialect surprises.

For mocking downstream HTTP calls, use `MockRestServiceServer` when you inject `RestTemplate`, or `WireMock` (via `wiremock-spring-boot-starter`) for `WebClient`/`RestClient` scenarios. WireMock runs an embedded HTTP server, so your client code exercises real serialization and error handling.

Slice tests cut startup cost dramatically: `@WebMvcTest` loads only the web layer (controllers, filters, `@ControllerAdvice`), while `@DataJpaTest` spins only JPA infrastructure with a transaction-scoped rollback per test. Use `@MockBean` to stub collaborators in slice tests — it replaces the bean in the Spring context, unlike plain Mockito mocks. Combine slices for targeted, fast coverage without the overhead of a full `@SpringBootTest`.$escape$,
  $escape$@SpringBootTest
@AutoConfigureTestDatabase(replace = AutoConfigureTestDatabase.Replace.NONE)
@Testcontainers
class OrderServiceIT {

    @Container
    static PostgreSQLContainer<?> postgres =
        new PostgreSQLContainer<>("postgres:16-alpine");

    @DynamicPropertySource
    static void props(DynamicPropertyRegistry r) {
        r.add("spring.datasource.url", postgres::getJdbcUrl);
        r.add("spring.datasource.username", postgres::getUsername);
        r.add("spring.datasource.password", postgres::getPassword);
    }

    @Autowired OrderService orderService;

    @Test
    void createsOrder() {
        var order = orderService.create(new OrderRequest("item-1", 2));
        assertThat(order.id()).isNotNull();
    }
}$escape$,
  $escape$kotlin$escape$,
