INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '6733055e-2e63-47a2-b46f-6408cd01af58',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$Spring Boot DevTools — Hot Reload, LiveReload, and the Restart Classloader Explained$escape$,
  $escape$Spring Boot DevTools gives you two distinct reload mechanisms, and knowing the difference matters. The **restart** classloader watches your classpath for changes and restarts the application context — but only the "restart" classloader reloads, while the "base" classloader (third-party jars) stays warm. This makes restarts roughly 2–3x faster than a cold start. The **LiveReload** server (port 35729) pushes browser refreshes automatically when static resources or templates change — no restart needed.

Add DevTools to any Spring Boot project via the `spring-boot-devtools` dependency (scope `runtime`, optional). For property changes to take effect without restart, mark them in `spring.devtools.restart.additional-paths`. To exclude noisy directories like `static/` from triggering restarts, use `spring.devtools.restart.exclude`.

For scaffolding, `spring initializr` via `curl` or the `spring` CLI (`spring init --dependencies=web,data-jpa,devtools myapp`) generates a production-ready project skeleton in seconds. Combine with IntelliJ's "Build project automatically" + Registry flag `compiler.automake.allow.when.app.running` and you get near-continuous hot reload without any manual trigger.$escape$,
  $escape$# Bootstrap a project with DevTools via Spring CLI
spring init \
  --dependencies=web,data-jpa,devtools,lombok \
  --java-version=21 \
  --build=maven \
  --name=demo \
  demo-app

# application.properties — tune restart behavior
spring.devtools.restart.exclude=static/**,public/**
spring.devtools.restart.additional-paths=src/main/resources
spring.devtools.livereload.enabled=true$escape$,
  $escape$bash$escape$,
